				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Lag while kiting<a name="33552"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Apr 8 04 9:50 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I found memory to be the key. Although I use an Athlon 2600XP+. I gave a friend 256MB of my Mem so now I'm down to 512MB. Made a difference. Once memory prices drop again I'm going to 1GB. I use a RADEON 9600 Pro, but the 9500 is a nice card as well. Bought the 9600 for dx9 compatibility. Memory Memory Memory is all I can say. Also check your swap file and adjust the size. Do you see your disk led mashing while kiting? Customize that and things oughta be a bit smoother. Also eliminate any background apps on your startup. You need all the resources you can get.
<br />
Just my 2cp worth
<br />

<br />
</span></td>
